  <h3 id="ChangeRenditionMode">Change rendition mode of letter</h3> 
  <p>By default, the Create Correspondence UI uses the HTML or mobile forms to render the letter preview. The mobile forms preview has no issues rendering in any browser, as it uses the browser's native plug-in and requires no additional plug-ins. You can change the letter preview mode to PDF. However, browser constraints may create issues for different features of the interactive PDF preview of the letter. </p> 
  <p>For more information on browser compatibility with letter preview, see <a href="https://helpx.adobe.com/aem-forms/kb/discontinuation-of-npapi-plugins-impact-on-aem-forms.html" target="_blank">Discontinuation of NPAPI browser plug-ins and its impact</a>.</p> 
  <p>To change the preview mode of the letter, complete the following steps:</p> 
  <ol> 
   <li><p style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">Go to <span class="kbd">http://[system]:[port]/system/console/configMgr</span> and, if necessary, log in as Admin.</p> </li> 
   <li><p>Go to <span class="uicontrol">Correspondence Management Configurations</span> &amp;gt; <span class="uicontrol">Rendition Type</span> and select <strong>HTML Rendition</strong> (Default) or <strong>PDF Rendition</strong>. </p> </li> 
   <li><p>Click <strong><span class="uicontrol">Save</span></strong>.</p> </li> 
  </ol> 
